commit.message: Add GitHub Actions setting file
Fix emojify-reveal-on-isearch defcustom type
Update the url for openmoji
add OpenMoji license to README
add version number
add openmoji-v13.0 to known emoji sets
Update the docstring of `emojify-completing-read` to mention new API for the predicate

Silence byte-compiler

Define alias before referents
Guard against empty strings while emojifying company tooltips
add: use-package snippet in readme
Whoops; forgot to remove this…
Revert this back to `completing-read`.
Actually be able to call this, rather than causing an error…
Change this to a list, rather than modify the hash table later.

And then we've gotta modify the `candidates` so they can work with
functions like `ido-completing-read`.

And update the documentation; we won't mention that
`emojify-completing-read-function` takes the same arguments as
`completing-read` since they can click through to read that from
`emojify-completing-read-function`'s documentation.
Replace all locations of `completing-read` with the new variable.

We'll allow the user to set the function themselves; they just have to
assure that the arguments of the function match what `completing-read` accepts.
Improve test for org-mode tag detection
Disable emojis in deft-mode
Fix the regex used to identity org-mode tags
Bump version

Disable `buffer-list-update-hook` in emojify-string

Since the function creates a temporary buffer, the hook gets invoked
unnecessarily confusing EXWM's focus tracking code, which makes it impossible to
switch between X11 frames

Iterate through emojis from end to beginning in emojify-do-for-emojis-in-region

This allows `forms` passed to `emojify-do-for-emojis-in-region` to be
potentially mutate the buffer without the other emoji positions becoming invalid
Fix a few typos
Escape literal '%' in result of format-mode-line
Add a compatibility wrapper over org-src-get-lang-mode
